    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The root-locus plot of a closed-loop system with unity negative feedback and transfer function KG(s) in the forward path is shown in the figure. Note that K is varied from 0 to $$\\infty$$.</p>\n<p>Select the transfer function G(s) that results in the root-locus plot of the closed-loop system as shown in the figure.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7idrszq/1f709677-2da2-47d6-b3a0-8a817e6923bf/1938d970-2997-11ed-bc1c-a3a2358ae168/file-1l7idrszr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7idrszq/1f709677-2da2-47d6-b3a0-8a817e6923bf/1938d970-2997-11ed-bc1c-a3a2358ae168/file-1l7idrszr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2022 Control Systems - Root Locus Diagram Question 4 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$G(s) = {1 \\over {{{(s + 1)}^5}}}$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$G(s) = {1 \\over {{s^5} + 1}}$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$G(s) = {{s - 1} \\over {{{(s + 1)}^6}}}$$"
