    "content": "<p>The pole-zero map of a rational function $G(s)$ is shown below. When the closed contour $\\Gamma$ is mapped into $G(s)$-plane, then the mapping encircles</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh201y3o/b041a3e3-09af-4c41-8474-f50045eaf47d/dc7dd150-af46-11f0-ba93-393527bdf085/file-jaoe38c1mh201y3p.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh201y3o/b041a3e3-09af-4c41-8474-f50045eaf47d/dc7dd150-af46-11f0-ba93-393527bdf085/file-jaoe38c1mh201y3p.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2020 Control Systems - Root Locus Diagram Question 2 English\">",
